<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583715>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 2. Dactylogyrus oryziasi n. sp., paratype (NSMT-Pl 6292) for A, N, holotype (NSMT-Pl 6291) for B–M, O. A, whole mount (ventral view); B, anchor; C, dorsal bar; D, ventral bar; E, marginal hook pair I; F, marginal hook pair II; G, marginal hook pair III; H, marginal hook pair IV; I, marginal hook pair V; J, marginal hook pair VI; K, marginal hook pair VII; L, needle; M, male copulatory organ (dorsal view); N, male genital organs (ventral view); O, vagina (dorsal view). Scale bars: A, 50µm; B–O, 10µm. Abbreviations: an, anchor; ap, accessory piece; e, eye; h, haptor; hg, haptoral grand; ho, head organ; i, intestine; mg, Mehlis’ gland; mh, marginal hook; n, needle; o, oötype; od, oviduct; ov, ovary; p, penis; ph, pharynx; pr, prostatic reservoir; sv, seminal vesicle; t, testis; v, vagina; vd, vas deferens; vl, vitellaria; vo, vaginal opening." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4583715/files/figure.png" .

